Here are some lists I've compiled of my most referenced and shared resources:

## Data Democratization & Data Equity

-   [**Principles for Using Public Health Data to Drive Equity**](https://www.cdcfoundation.org/data-equity-principles?inline) developed by CDC Foundation
-   [**A Toolkit for Centering Racial Equity Throughout Data Integration**](https://www.aecf.org/resources/a-toolkit-for-centering-racial-equity-within-data-integration) developed by Actionable Intelligence for Social Policy
-   [**A Health Equity Framework**](https://www.mass.gov/doc/health-equity-framework-compendium/download) developed by the Massachusetts Health Policy Commission
-   [**Charting a Course for an Equity-Centered Data System**](https://www.rwjf.org/en/insights/our-research/2021/10/charting-a-course-for-an-equity-centered-data-system.html) developed by the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation
-   [**Data Commitment and Principles**](https://www.phidenverhealth.org/about-us/health-equity/data-commitment-and-principles) developed by the Denver Public Health Department
-   [**Data Democratization: The Unsung Hero Of Health Equity**](https://healthleadsusa.org/communications-center/blog/data-democratization-the-unsung-hero-of-health-equity) developed by Health Leads
-   [**Health Data Governance Principles**](https://www.healthdataprinciples.org/principles) developed by Transform Health
-   [**Equitable Evaluation Framework**](https://www.equitableeval.org/framework) developed by the Equitable Evaluation Initiative
-   [**On Racism: A New Standard for Publishing On Racial Health Inequities**](https://www.healthaffairs.org/do/10.1377/forefront.20200630.939347/) authored by Rhea Boyd

## R

-   [**Epidemiologist R Handbook**](https://epirhandbook.com/en/) by Neale Batra et al. at Applied Epi
-   [**Advanced R**](https://adv-r.hadley.nz/) by Hadley Wickham
-   [**Big Book of R**](https://www.bigbookofr.com/) by Oscar Baruffa
-   [**R for Data Science (2nd Edition)**](https://r4ds.hadley.nz/) by Hadley Wickham, Mine Cetinkaya-Rundel, and Garrett Grolemund
-   [**Cheatsheets**](https://posit.co/blog/cheat-sheet-updates/) by Posit

## Data Visualization

-   [**Do No Harm Guide: Applying Equity Awareness in Data Visualization**](https://www.urban.org/research/publication/do-no-harm-guide-applying-equity-awareness-data-visualization) developed by Urban Institute
-   [**Powering Health Equity Action with Online Data Tools: 10 Design Principles**](https://nationalequityatlas.org/sites/default/files/10-Design-Principles-For-Online-Data-Tools.pdf) developed by PolicyLink and Ecotrust
-   [**ColorBrewer**](https://colorbrewer2.org) developed by Cynthia Brewer and Mark Harrower
-   [**Accessibility and Visualization**](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KVisPxjgdtU) by Frank Elavsky
-   [**Chartability**](https://www.frank.computer/chartability/) by Frank Elavsky, Cynthia Bennett, and Dominik Moritz

## Code Style

-   [**naming things**](https://www2.stat.duke.edu/~rcs46/lectures_2015/01-markdown-git/slides/naming-slides/naming-slides.pdf) by Jenny Bryan
